  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Major interest in our investigation is to find out whether distinct fixation techniques
      influence catheter dislocation and/ or incidence of local inflammation. A systematic
      comparison of two different fixation techniques with regard to catheter location, analgetic
      potential and signs of local inflammation will be conducted. To ensure identical patients
      groups allocation will be strictly randomized. Furthermore, both patient groups will receive
      identical pain medication via the peridural catheter in situ. All catheter tips will be
      screened microbiologically after removal.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
